Hosted by Educational Outreach Director Indira Sukhraj, this featured 45-minute faculty workshop will cover being involved in the community, sharing your passion for STEM, age-targeted teaching tactics, and more!

Come participate live in IST-1001! This workshop will not be available virtually.

Hosted by Nick Stafford, this hour-long workshop is the first part of our PC Building trilogy and will teach you all about part compatibility, knowing your model numbers, planning a build on a budget, and more!

Come see it live in IST-1017 and on Teams!

Register Now on our Workshops Page

Hosted by professor and industry expert Dr. Bruce Jacob, this featured hour-long faculty workshop will cover not only the thought processes necessary to get started with making and selling your own product, but also the process of design and iteration that will lead you to an end product people want to give you money for.

Come participate live in IST-1060 or on Teams!

Register Now on our Workshops Page

Hosted by Amanda Coleman, this 30-minute workshop will teach you all about how to get started with Git, GitHub, and version control, plus the basics for working with a shared or evolving programming project!

Come see it live in IST-1064 and on Teams!
